me: *sees them using a scratch (a programme that first used this style to help people learn) based software to script a wand and then its labelled as coding.
also me: this isnt coding i have coded discord bots with java script on visual studio and done a little on html and a tiny bit of c++ and c#, thats coding, this is more of a basic jigsaw puzzle for beginners thats classed as code, tho it is technically code and has a few aspects that are similar in some cases to advanced code it doesnt help for the majority of advanced coding especially if your debugger doesnt work so you have to manually run through your script/code and edit what you think is wrong until the code works, so the programme scratch does help a little but manually debugging code even if its other peoples old codes that have slight errors will help you learn much more
